{"title_page": "Sacramento County Sheriff's Department", "text_new": "{{Unbalanced|date=May 2010}}\n\n{{Infobox Law enforcement agency\n| agencyname      = Sacramento County Sheriff's Office\n| nativename      =\n| nativenamea     =\n| nativenamer     =\n| commonname      =\n| abbreviation    = SSO\n| fictional       =\n| patch           = Patch of the Sacramento County Sheriff's Department.png\n| patchcaption    =\n| logo            = Seal of the Sacramento County Sheriff's Department.png\n| logocaption     = Seal of the Sacramento County Sheriff's Department\n| badge           = \n| badgecaption    =\n| flag            =\n| flagcaption     =\n| imagesize       =\n| motto           = \"Service with Concern!\"\n| mottotranslated =\n| mission         =\n| formedyear      = 1850\n| formedmonthday  =\n| preceding1      =\n| dissolved       =\n| superseding     =\n| employees       =\n| volunteers      =\n| budget          = $403 million (2011-2012)<!-- $368,466,473 for Sheriff, $34,600,394 for correctional health -->\n| nongovernment   =\n| country         = United States\n| countryabbr     = U.S.\n| national        =\n| federal         =\n| international   =\n| divtype         = State\n| divname         = California\n| divdab          =\n| subdivtype      = \n| subdivname      = Sacramento\n| subdivdab       =\n| map             = Map of California highlighting Sacramento County.svg\n| mapcaption      =\n| sizearea        = {{convert|995|sqmi|km2}}\n| sizepopulation  = 2,000,000\n| legaljuris      =\n| governingbody   =\n| governingbodyscnd =\n| constitution1   =\n| police          = Yes\n| local           = Yes\n| military        =\n| provost         =\n| gendarmerie     =\n| religious       =\n| speciality      =\n| secret          =\n| overviewtype    =\n| overviewbody    =\n| headquarters    = [[Sacramento, California]]\n| hqlocmap        =\n| hqlocleft       =\n| hqloctop        =\n| hqlocmappoptitle =\n| sworntype       =\n| sworn           =\n| unsworntype     =\n| unsworn         =\n| multinational   =\n| electeetype     =\n| minister1name   =\n| minister1pfo    =\n| chief1name      = [[Scott Jones (U.S. politician)|Scott Jones]]\n| chief1position  = [[Sheriff]]\n| parentagency    =\n| child1agency    =\n| unittype        =\n| unitname        =\n| officetype      =\n| officename      =\n| provideragency  =\n| uniformedas     =\n| stationtype     = Station\n| stations        = 6\n| airbases        =\n| lockuptype      = Jail\n| lockups         = 2\n| vehicle1type    =\n| vehicles1       =\n| boat1type       =\n| boats1          =\n| aircraft1type   = Helicopter\n| aircraft1       = 4\n| animal1type     =\n| animals1        =\n| person1name     =\n| person1reason   =\n| person1type     =\n| programme1      =\n| activity1name   =\n| activitytype    =\n| anniversary1    =\n| award1          =\n| website         = [http://www.sacsheriff.com/ Official website]\n| footnotes       =\n| reference       =\n}}\n\nThe '''Sacramento County Sheriff's Department''' ('''SSD'''), is a local law enforcement agency that serves [[Sacramento County, California]]. It provides general-service law enforcement to unincorporated areas of Sacramento County, as well as [[incorporation (municipal government)|incorporated]] cities within the county that have contracted with the agency for law-enforcement services. Currently only [[Rancho Cordova, California|Rancho Cordova]], and [[Isleton, California|Isleton]]  has such a contract with the department since the [[Citrus Heights, California|Citrus Heights]] and [[Elk Grove, California|Elk Grove]] Police Departments assumed all police authority and responsibility for their communities in 2006. It also holds primary jurisdiction over facilities operated by Sacramento County, such as local parks, marinas, and government buildings{{Citation needed|date=March 2011}}; provides marshal service for the [[Sacramento County Superior Court]]; operates the [[Sacramento County Jail]] and the Rio Cosumnes Correctional Center in Elk Grove; and provides services such as laboratories and academy training to smaller law-enforcement agencies within the county. The [[county sheriff]] is currently [[Scott Jones (U.S. politician)|Scott Jones]].\n\n==Weapons==\nThe Sacramento Sheriff's department currently issues versions of the 9mm Glock. Deputies also have less lethal items that are issued to them including but not limited to an X26 taser, expandable baton, and OC spray.\n\n==Organization==\n<big>'''Sheriff Scott Jones'''</big>\n\n'''Office of the Sheriff'''\n:[http://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/Community/CommunityRelations.aspx Community Relations Unit]\n:Legislative Affairs\n:Media and Public Affairs\n:[http://www.socab.saccounty.net/pages/default.htm Sheriff's Outreach Community Advisory Board]{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n:[http://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/SIIB/SIIB/aspx Special Investigations/Intelligence Bureau]\n::[https://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/SIIB/Bingo.aspx Bingo Licensing]\n::ATF Task Force\n::Anti-Terrorism\n::Business License/Labor Relations\n::Criminal Intelligence/Organized Crime\n::F.B.I. Joint Terrorism Task Force\n::Gambling/Vice Operations\n::[https://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/SIIB/CCW.aspx Gun Permits]\n::Pawn/Secondhand Dealers\n:\n'''Office of the Undersheriff - Erik Maness'''\n:Fleet Services\n:\n'''Contract and Regional Services'''\n:[https://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/Airport/Airport.aspx Airport Division]\n:[https://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/CorrectionalCourt/civil.aspx Civil Bureau]\n:[https://www.sacsheriff.com/Pages/Organization/Court_Security/CourtSecurity.aspx Court Security Division]\n::B.T. Collins Juvenile Courthouse\n::Carol Miller Justice Center\n::Gordon D. Schaber Facility\n::William R. Ridgeway Family Relations Court\n:Folsom Dam Bureau\n:Security Services\n::Children's Services\n::DA\n::DHA\n::DHHS\n::Regional Transit Police Ser