{"title_page": "Carrickshock GAA", "text_new": "{{Infobox GAA club\n| club gaa    = Carrickshock\n| irish       = Carraig Seac \n| crest       = \n| founded     = 1928 \n| province    = Leinster \n| county      = Kilkenny \n| nickname    = 'Shock \n| colours     = Green and gold\n| grounds     = Hugginstown \n| coordinates = {{coord|52|27|20.16|N|7|13|27.91|W|display=it|region:IE_type:landmark}}\n| h3          = 7\n| pattern_la  = \n| pattern_b   = _goldrightsash\n| pattern_ra  = \n| leftarm     = 008000\n| body        = 008000 \n| rightarm    = 008000\n| shorts      = FFFFFF \n| socks       = 008000\n|}}\n'''Carrickshock''' is an Irish [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] club situated in the south of [[County Kilkenny]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. The club was founded in 1928<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=37 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-06-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302100731/http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=37 |archivedate=2009-03-02 }}</ref> when the teams from [[Hugginstown]] and [[Knockmoylan]] were amalgamated in commemoration of the [[Carrickshock incident|Battle of Carrickshock]], 1831.\n\nCarrickshock have had success in the [[Kilkenny Senior Hurling Championship]], winning the competition seven times. Their record of four county titles in a row between 1940 and 1943 remained unbroken until 2009 when [[Ballyhale Shamrocks]] won their 4th title in succession.\n\nMany players from the club have gone to achieve success with the [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] intercounty team.\n\n== Honours ==\n*'''[[Kilkenny Senior Hurling Championship]]s:''' 7\n** 1931, 1938, 1940, 1941, 1942, 1943, 1951  \n* Runners-up: \n** 1929, 1932, 1933, 1934, 1935, 1939, 1944, 1945, 1946, 1948, 2010, 2013 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/hurling/clara-pull-off-seismic-shock-247658.html |title=Clara pull off seismic shock |accessdate=28 October 2013 |work=[[Irish Examiner]] |publisher= |date=28 October 2013}}</ref>\n* '''Kilkenny Senior Hurling League''' \n** 2012<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/hurling/carrickshock-shape-up-for-county-tilt-with-league-title-win-210868.html |title=Carrickshock shape up for county tilt with league title win |date=2012-10-15|work=Irish Examiner|accessdate=2012-10-15}}</ref>\n*'''Kilkenny Minor Hurling Championships:''' 2\n** 2001, 2002\n* '''[[All-Ireland Intermediate Club Hurling Championship]]''' 1\n** 2017<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/carrickshock-power-proves-too-much-for-galway-outfit-443364.html|title=Carrickshock power proves too much for Galway outfit |accessdate=21 February 2017 |work=[[Irish Examiner]] |publisher= |date=20 February 2017}}</ref>\n*'''[[Leinster Intermediate Club Hurling Championship]]''' 2\n** 2004, 2016<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/hurling/rohan-shocks-brave-celbridge-35267764.html |title=Rohan shocks brave Celbridge|accessdate=5 December 2016 |work=[[Irish Independent]] |publisher= |date= 5 December 2016}}</ref>\n*'''[[Kilkenny Intermediate Hurling Championship]]s:''' 2\n** 2004, 2016<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hoganstand.com/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=262944|title=Power helps Carrickshock back to the big time |accessdate=7 November 2016 |work=[[Hogan Stand]] |publisher= |date= 7 November 2016}}</ref>\n*'''[[Kilkenny Junior Hurling Championship]]s:''' 4\n** 1928, 1954, 1979, 1999\n\n== Famous hurlers ==\n* [[Richie Power (1957)|Richie Power]] \n* [[Pat Dwyer (hurler)|Pat Dwyer]]\n* [[Jimmy Walsh (Kilkenny hurler)|Jimmy Walsh]]  \n* [[John Tennyson]]\n* [[John Dalton (hurler)|John Dalton]]\n* [[Richie Power (1985)|Richie Power]]\n* [[John Power (Carrickshock hurler)|John Power]]\n* [[Michael Rice (Irish sportsman)|Michael Rice]]\n* [[Sean O' (John) Farrell]] (1909-72), 1933<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.kilkennygaa.ie/gallery/index/category/12|title = All Albums > Kilkenny All Ireland Winning Teams > All Ireland SH Champions > Senior winning Teams 1931 to 1960|date = |accessdate = |website = The Official Kilkenny GAA Website|publisher = Kilkenny GAA|last = |first = }}</ref>\nLuke \u2018DickPic\u2019 Hudson\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090622041115/http://carrickshock.kilkenny.gaa.ie/ Carrickshock on the official Kilkenny website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090302100731/http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=37 Information about Carrickshock on the KilkennyCats website]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kilkenny GAA clubs}}\n\n[[Category:Gaelic Athletic Association clubs in County Kilkenny]]\n[[Category:Hurling clubs in County Kilkenny]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox GAA club\n| club gaa    = Carrickshock\n| irish       = Carraig Seac \n| crest       = \n| founded     = 1928 \n| province    = Leinster \n| county      = Kilkenny \n| nickname    = 'Shock \n| colours     = Green and gold\n| grounds     = Hugginstown \n| coordinates = {{coord|52|27|20.16|N|7|13|27.91|W|display=it|region:IE_type:landmark}}\n| h3          = 7\n| pattern_la  = \n| pattern_b   = _goldrightsash\n| pattern_ra  = \n| leftarm     = 008000\n| body        = 008000 \n| rightarm    = 008000\n| shorts      = FFFFFF \n| socks       = 008000\n|}}\n'''Carrickshock''' is an Irish [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] club situated in the south of [[County Kilkenny]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. The club was founded in 1928<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=37 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-06-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302100731/http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=37 |archivedate=2009-03-02 }}</ref> when the teams from [[Hugginstown]] and [[Knockmoylan]] were amalgamated in commemoration of the [[Carrickshock incident|Battle of Carrickshock]], 1831.\n\nCarrickshock have had success in the [[Kilkenny Senior Hurling Championship]], winning the competition seven times. Their record of four county titles in a row between 1940 and 1943 remained unbroken until 2009 when [[Ballyhale Shamrocks]] won their 4th title in succession.\n\nMany players from the club have gone to achieve success with the [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] intercounty team.\n\n== Honours ==\n*'''[[Kilkenny Senior Hurling Championship]]s:''' 7\n** 1931, 1938, 1940, 1941, 1942, 1943, 1951  \n* Runners-up: \n** 1929, 1932, 1933, 1934, 1935, 1939, 1944, 1945, 1946, 1948, 2010, 2013 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/hurling/clara-pull-off-seismic-shock-247658.html |title=Clara pull off seismic shock |accessdate=28 October 2013 |work=[[Irish Examiner]] |publisher= |date=28 October 2013}}</ref>\n* '''Kilkenny Senior Hurling League''' \n** 2012<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/hurling/carrickshock-shape-up-for-county-tilt-with-league-title-win-210868.html |title=Carrickshock shape up for county tilt with league title win |date=2012-10-15|work=Irish Examiner|accessdate=2012-10-15}}</ref>\n*'''Kilkenny Minor Hurling Championships:''' 2\n** 2001, 2002\n* '''[[All-Ireland Intermediate Club Hurling Championship]]''' 1\n** 2017<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/carrickshock-power-proves-too-much-for-galway-outfit-443364.html|title=Carrickshock power proves too much for Galway outfit |accessdate=21 February 2017 |work=[[Irish Examiner]] |publisher= |date=20 February 2017}}</ref>\n*'''[[Leinster Intermediate Club Hurling Championship]]''' 2\n** 2004, 2016<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/hurling/rohan-shocks-brave-celbridge-35267764.html |title=Rohan shocks brave Celbridge|accessdate=5 December 2016 |work=[[Irish Independent]] |publisher= |date= 5 December 2016}}</ref>\n*'''[[Kilkenny Intermediate Hurling Championship]]s:''' 2\n** 2004, 2016<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hoganstand.com/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=262944|title=Power helps Carrickshock back to the big time |accessdate=7 November 2016 |work=[[Hogan Stand]] |publisher= |date= 7 November 2016}}</ref>\n*'''[[Kilkenny Junior Hurling Championship]]s:''' 4\n** 1928, 1954, 1979, 1999\n\n== Famous hurlers ==\n* [[Richie Power (1957)|Richie Power]] \n* [[Pat Dwyer (hurler)|Pat Dwyer]]\n* [[Jimmy Walsh (Kilkenny hurler)|Jimmy Walsh]]  \n* [[John Tennyson]]\n* [[John Dalton (hurler)|John Dalton]]\n* [[Richie Power (1985)|Richie Power]]\n* [[John Power (Carrickshock hurler)|John Power]]\n* [[Michael Rice (Irish sportsman)|Michael Rice]]\n* [[Sean O' (John) Farrell]] (1909-72), 1933<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.kilkennygaa.ie/gallery/index/category/12|title = All Albums > Kilkenny All Ireland Winning Teams > All Ireland SH Champions > Senior winning Teams 1931 to 1960|date = |accessdate = |website = The Official Kilkenny GAA Website|publisher = Kilkenny GAA|last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090622041115/http://carrickshock.kilkenny.gaa.ie/ Carrickshock on the official Kilkenny website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090302100731/http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=37 Information about Carrickshock on the KilkennyCats website]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kilkenny GAA clubs}}\n\n[[Category:Gaelic Athletic Association clubs in County Kilkenny]]\n[[Category:Hurling clubs in County Kilkenny]]\n", "name_user": "78.19.219.188", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eFamous hurlers)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carrickshock_GAA"}
